  "prompt": "In IIT Bombay medical studies are there or not?",
  "response": "Yes, IIT Bombay does have some involvement in medical studies, primarily through interdisciplinary research and collaborations rather than offering a full-fledged medical degree (like MBBS). Here are some details:\n\n1. **Interdisciplinary Programs**: IIT Bombay offers programs like **Biosciences and Bioengineering** that intersect with medical studies. Students can engage in research related to healthcare, medical devices, and biomedical technologies.\n\n2. **Collaborations**: IIT Bombay collaborates with institutions like the **Tata Memorial Centre (TMC)** and **Homi Bhabha National Institute (HBNI)** for cancer research and other medical-related studies.\n\n3. **Medical Technology**: The institute focuses on developing medical devices, diagnostics, and healthcare technologies through its departments like Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, and Centre for Research in Nanotechnology & Science (CRNTS).\n\n4. **Short-term Courses and Workshops**: IIT Bombay occasionally offers workshops and courses related to medical technology and healthcare for students and professionals.\n\nHowever, if you are looking for a traditional medical degree (MBBS), you would need to consider **All India Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS)** or other medical colleges, as IIT Bombay does not offer MBBS or MD programs.",
